I have completed the Kafka Connect and IBM MQ **NEFT** configuration on OpenShift and shared the related YAML files (KafkaConnect, MQ Source, MQ Sink) for review. The setup is aligned with our Kafka (Strimzi, KRaft) architecture and is ready for validation.

As discussed earlier with **Baboo sir**, the **RTGS flow is not configured yet**, as we are still awaiting clarity on RTGS queue/channel details from the MQ side. For now, the implementation and testing are limited to **NEFT only**.

Currently, we are blocked because the **AMQ Streams (Strimzi) operator is down** in the cluster. The operator pod is in `ImagePullBackOff` state due to a registry image pull issue. Until the operator is up and running, KafkaConnect pods cannot be created, and connector testing cannot proceed.

The OpenShift admin team has been informed and is working on fixing the operator issue (image mirroring / registry access).

Once the operator is restored, KafkaConnect pods should come up automatically and we can immediately proceed with **NEFT MQ → Kafka → MQ end-to-end testing**. RTGS can be taken up after the required details are confirmed.

